      "text": "Another approach to motivating people to change is to create a \"burning platform.\" The concept of a burning platform comes from the analogy of standing on an oil platform at sea that's on fire - the urgency to save yourself is so great you take action and jump off. In business, burning platform is a term used to describe the process of helping people see the dire consequences of not changing. By sparking just enough concern about what happens if the status quo remains the same, people embrace change. The problem with this approach is that people don't know what lies on the other side of the change. [https://www.inc.com/soren-kaplan/4-steps-to-create-a-burning-platform-to-motivate-change.html source]"
